hello! long-time reader, first-time skipper!

i wanted to make something gripping in honor of July 4, the most terrifying time of yearso I wrote up an article about the scariest thing I could think of: a city government's intern forgetting his backpack.

(The source for the page's lone image is https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Judiciary_Square_station_entrance_pylon.jpg, which is in the public domain.)

thanks for your time!

EDIT: also! big ups to IHP and QuantumSpace for checking out my draft (and being patient with me while I flailed confusedly around IRC for the first time)!

EDIT EDIT: the article's image has been changed; the new image's source is https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Lever_arch_file.jpg, taken by Pavel Kronk and covered by the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 2.5 Generic license. (I've also made a few minor edits and added a classified banner; thanks to aismallard for pointing me to the SCP style resource and making some formatting edits!)





