For a first time work, this is pretty great. I like the confusion with something that just feels so anomalous, but evidently isn't. You can see the human element of the Foundation, as people's information is scrutinized or revealed and people feel vulnerable over the very existence of this document. The implicit suggestion of blackmail was also great.

Or I'm just a sucker for -EX scips. Either way, +1.

That said, there are a lot of small weaknesses that bring this article short of greatness.

+nitpicks

-nitpicks




Explained/Neutralized
附加记录：    

Object classifications are for determining difficulty of containment, if an object is not considered to be anomalous, whether it's  implies it was once anomalous, here, it never was.



The Judiciary Square neighborhood of Washington, D.C. SCP-5297-EX was recovered several hundred meters from the location of this photograph.
附加记录：    

Given you explain the discovery later, I would just make this .



Site 01
附加记录：    

Site-01. Though generally note you don't store anomalies at green sites, though I'm willing to let this pass since it's not clear when they discovered it wasn't anomalous.



POI-5297-1
附加记录：    

It's usually PoI. Also not sure why it's -1, given there isn't a PoI -2. Imo it should just be PoI-5297, but that doesn't matter too much.



Update1/15/2019
附加记录：    

You should use the international date standard to avoid confusion between American and European-style dates.



including several whose documentation is classified Level 4 or Level 5.
附加记录：    

Level-4 or Level-5. Also I would consider saying 



prominent SCP Foundation officials.
附加记录：    

I found it kind of weird that you call it the  for this one line, to no apparent effect.



The MTF units moved to apprehend him. After a brief conversation, POI-5297-1 sent a text message to an unknown person and left the building.
附加记录：    

I think this could be cleared up a bit without being too explicit. As far as I can tell, what happened here is that PoI-5297 told something compromising to the task force to get them to release him.










